		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Tony+Isaac">Tony Isaac</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Tony+Isaac">( 1301187 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64624753"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64624753"><p>100+ years ago, a 7-day work week was common. "Good" businesses gave people one day off per week. Then Henry Ford came along and popularized the five-day work week, as a way to encourage people to take road trips in the cars he sold them. <a href="https://firmspace.com/theproworker/from-strikes-to-labor-laws-how-the-us-adopted-the-5-day-workweek" title="firmspace.com">https://firmspace.com/theprowo...</a> [firmspace.com] Everybody thought it was fantastic...until a five day work week became normal.</p><p>The same will happen to a 4-day work week. People will think it's great, until it becomes normal, and then the same old grumpiness will set in.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64624753">

